$interpreted: Miranda: Darnit, all these Panther houses look the same...
Panther Thug: Why's it smell like dirty humans? Hey!
Miranda: Wonderful! Are you here to take me to the matriarch?
Panther Thug: Eh? Do we look like stupid idiots? Open your eyes dumb broad, before you get yourself hurt!
Miranda: ...Uh, is there something I can help you with?
Panther Mafioso: Heard you want to join the East Alliance Martial Arts Tourney and you came here to borrow something of ours.
Miranda: That's right. I'll win for sure.
Panther Thug: Hahaha, good joke. Whatta ya say, boss?
Panther Mafioso: Haha, very funny.
Panther Mafioso: A mere human, beating beasts? Quit dreaming! If you don't want something bad to happen, you best leave now!
Miranda: I almost forgot there were beasts like you...
Panther Thug: Huh? What'd you say?

Miranda: I am Miranda, disciple of Law, Grandmaster of the Wolf Tribe.

I formally challenge you to determine who's skills reign supreme. Remember, this is not a fight to the death.
Miranda: An injury may be difficult to prevent...so if you're scared, you may refuse.
Panther Mafioso: You think I'm scared of you, ya rotten human!
Miranda: The winner has been decided. That was a good fight!
Panther Thug: Waaaaahhh!
Miranda: If Master didn't always remind me to control my temper...
Miranda: I'd teach these discriminating beasts a lesson for sure, I would!
Fatima: ...For a human, you're quite skilled.
Mother Liukanee: Yes...
Miranda: Miss Matriarch, what did you find?
Mother Liukanee: ...Aigh, Fatima. Grandmother is thirsty.
Mother Liukanee: This human is Me...me what?
Fatima: Miranda.
Mother Liukanee: Ah, yes~ Now I remember.
Mother Liukanee: This young damsel named Miranny, what she speaks is true.
Fatima: ......

Mother Liukanee: The ancient manuscripts record that each of the major tribes in the East Alliance possessed a wooden tablet. 

Made from the Udumbara tree, it contained abundant spiritual energy allowing it to exist without rotting.
Mother Liukanee: Later, the Panther tribe split it in two, one residing in the East Alliance and the Holy Talisman residing here with us.
Panther Officer: But Ancestral Mother, I've never heard of such a thing.
Mother Liukanee: The manuscripts state that this is because...um...
Mother Liukanee: ...Let Grandmother see...
Mother Liukanee: Ah, yes. Our ancestors took the Holy Talisman to the mountains to symbolize the Panther God that we worship, sealing it there.
Panther Officer: Ah, the forbidden area behind the mountain.
Mother Liukanee: Indeed. Before, the ancestors would perform ceremonies there regularly.
Mother Liukanee: Afterwards, things got better for the tribe and everybody began to forget. Before long...no one even remembered where it came from.
Miranda: Um, so can you give it to me?
Mother Liukanee: I suppose since we don't use it, we could lend it to you...
Mother Liukanee: But the ancient manuscripts indicate that if a Panther warrior wants to bear the Holy Talisman they must pass...a test.
Miranda: A test? What kind of test?
Mother Liukanee: Hmm...there was no description. I am not sure...
Mother Liukanee: What do you think? Shall we let this young one try?
Miranda: Yeah! I need this to compete. Of course I gotta take the test!
Panther Officer: Matriarch, humans cannot be trusted.
Panther Officer: If her master comes and can testify to her words, she still will have time to make it.
Mother Liukanee: Makes sense...Fatima, what do you think?
Fatima: ......
Miranda: I understand. I shall await my master's return.
Mother Liukanee: Wonderful, dear child. Just a few days wait.
Mother Liukanee: Ah, yes. What...What did you say your name was again?
